article.headline: IUPUI 88, S. Dakota 70
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Christian Siakam had 17 points and nine rebounds and Alex Young added 16 points, five assists and four steals as IUPUI defeated South Dakota 88-70 on Wednesday night. Sean Esposito scored 15 points and Stephen Thomas 14 for the Jaguars (12-16, 6-10 Summit League), who shot 60.3 percent (35 of 58) from the floor, including 10 of 17 from 3-point range. Louie Krogman had 24 points, seven assists and four steals, and Trevor Gruis added 15 points for the Coyotes (9-16, 4-12). The game got away from South Dakota late in the first half. Esposito and Young hit a 3-pointer each to key a 12-0 IUPUI run in a 2:19 stretch. The surge gave the Jaguars a 40-23 lead with 3:17 left in the half, and the Coyotes got no closer than 14 points afterward. IUPUI had a 31-25 rebounding edge and outscored South Dakota 44-28 in the paint. Charlie Westbrook scored 14 points for the Coyotes.
